53% of the patients admitted to the home of Victor-Gadboi come from their home, 47% come from the hospital.
Problem of access to palliative care
It is said that 77% of Canadians do not have access to palliative care, i.e. care that is supposed to alleviate the suffering of patients when the latter have reached the end stage of their lives, both at home, in the hospital or in a nursing home.
